headline: Zoetis (ZTS) Profit Margins Climb, Reinforcing Bullish Narratives Despite Premium Valuation
summary: Zoetis (ZTS) posted net profit margins of 28.2%, up from 26.6% last year, reflecting stronger profitability this period. Earnings have grown at 8.5% per year over the past five years, with a strong 9.1% uptick in the most recent year, outpacing the company’s historical average. Looking ahead, analysts expect annual earnings growth of 7.4%, trailing the broader US market’s 16% forecast, while revenue is projected to rise 5.2% per year, slower than the US average.
